## 🛠️ One-Time Post-Install Step for Kate LSP Integration
Kate contains an integrated LSP client plugin, but it must be enabled manually in the application settings interface after your first boot: [5, 6, 7, 8]

   1. Open Kate.
   2. Navigate to Settings → Configure Kate...
   3. Select Plugins from the left-hand column and click the checkbox next to LSP Client.
   4. Go to the new LSP Client settings page that appears in the sidebar and view the User Server Settings tab.
   5. Paste this quick JSON text layout to point Kate directly to the Nix Language Server you have deployed system-wide:

   {
       "servers": {
           "nix": {
               "command": ["nixd"],
               "root": "",
               "highlightingModeRegex": "^Nix$"
           }
       }
   }



💡 Quick Post-Install Slideshow Tips:

imv: Run imv -t 3 /path/to/folder in your terminal to start a loop where image files change automatically every 3 seconds.
nsxiv: Open a folder with nsxiv /path/to/folder, press Enter to open a picture, and press Ctrl+s to activate the automatic slideshow module.


💡 Dynamic Media-Key Mapping Tip (Post-Install)

Since you now have `playerctl` and are configuring **Niri**, you can link your physical keyboard media buttons (the ones that control volume and pause on headphones or keyboards) directly inside your `~/.config/niri/config.kdl` file like this:

binds {
    XF86AudioPlay  { spawn "playerctl" "play-pause"; }
    XF86AudioNext  { spawn "playerctl" "next"; }
    XF86AudioPrev  { spawn "playerctl" "previous"; }
}


This will let you skip tracks or pause your music instantly while inside terminal views or heavy fullscreen video games.
